text: Robert Robotham (by 1522 – 1570/71), of London, Hartington, Derbyshire and Raskelf, Yorkshire, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Reigate in March 1553, for Dorchester in 1555 and for Reading in 1563. ==References== Category:1570s deaths Category:Politicians from London Category:People from Hartington, Derbyshire Category:Politicians from Yorkshire Category:Year of birth uncertain Category:English MPs 1553 (Edward VI) Category:English MPs 1555 Category:English MPs 1563–1567 Category:Members of the Parliament of England for Dorchester
